messages.messageBody:
Less than a week, for those going to the HSC conference in Santa Clara, California

I realize this only applies to a dozen or thirty of you, and I'm sorry about that, but having the pre-first slot, Friday morning before the main speaker, the chances that people won't find out until later are extremely high.

*****I'm scheduled for a breakfast meeting, only in a conference room (the main room, Magnolia), 8:30 to 9:30 Friday.****

This meet-up with just be a question/answer session.

At 10:00 is the main speaker, Peggy O'Mara, so we can't go over time.
If you did want to bring food in there, get it very early.

Then I speak in that room at 11:45-1:00 so if you didn't have breakfast it will be a long time until lunch. Bring granola bars in your purse or something. :-)


All my sessions are in "Magnolia":


FRIDAY:

Breakfast talk 8:30-9:30
Connections 11:45-1:00

SATURDAY:

Seven Years of Learning Nothing (workshop) 4:15--5:30

SUNDAY:

Panel 10:00 - 11:15 Sue Patterson, Sandra Dodd, Pam Sorooshian, Pam Tellew

Perspective 2:30 - 4:00
[Where were you before (intellectually, emotionally, philosophically)? Where are you now? Where might you be next year, or in five years?]

Sorry, for those not going.
Sandra
